@BT 

Wrigley Field in Chicago has an iconic outfield wall because it is the only one covered in ivy vines.  That was probably an early attempt at padding the walls so that fielders didn't crash into them too hard.  Modern foam padding has solved that problem much better, so the ivy is actually less helpful these days, but Wrigley is all about tradition.

Of course, even here in the US, you'd have to be either a baseball fan or a Chicagoan to know this.  Lots of Americans are blissfully unaware of anything having to do with the sport, but for those in the know, it's perhaps the most iconic feature of any ballpark.

