@Charlie 
Amp is short for Amplifier. It's basically a little speaker for guitars and the like. While you would normally still use the signal from the guitar for the main PA, the Amp is normally still on and serves as a monitor (also a speaker) for the player. 

No complaints from a sound engineer here.

